---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import ProfilePhoto from '../assets/seungwon Kim profile photo.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Seungwon Kim — a model-based systems engineering consultant working across automotive, electronics, and defense, and exploring where MBSE meets AI."
	pubDate={new Date('June 14 2026')}
>
	<div class="profile">
		<Image src={ProfilePhoto} alt="Seungwon Kim" width={360} height={360} />
		<p class="name">Seungwon Kim</p>
	</div>

	<p>
		I take complex systems and turn them into something people can actually work with. Once a system
		grows large enough, no one can see the whole picture anymore — what connects to what gets lost. My
		job is to tie all of that into a single model that makes those connections visible. It's the kind
		of technical consulting usually called MBSE, or Model-Based Systems Engineering.
	</p>

	<p>
		There are two sides to the work. One is the engineer who takes a system apart and designs it; the
		other is the consultant who has to prove and sell that design in front of a customer. I move
		between the two. Lately, what interests me most is how AI is changing all of this — the way we
		design systems, and the way we explain them to other people, are both shifting fast.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is where I keep track of that change and write down what I've come to understand. Faced
		with a complex problem, I still tend to trust the model — and this is where I put that thinking.
	</p>

	<section class="cv">
		<h2>Experience</h2>
		<div class="cv-head">
			<span class="org">Dassault Systèmes</span>
			<span class="period">Feb 2020 – Present</span>
		</div>
		<p class="cv-sub">
			<strong>MBSE Industry Process Consultant</strong> · Sep 2021 – Present<br />
			MBSE consulting and proofs of concept for automotive, electronics, and defense customers —
			including Hyundai Motor, LG Electronics, Korea Aerospace Industries (KAI), and Hyundai Rotem.
			SysML-based system architecture, model-based simulation, and training.
		</p>
		<p class="cv-sub">
			<strong>ENOVIA Industry Process Consultant</strong> · Feb 2020 – Aug 2021<br />
			PLM/PDM solution proposals and PoC projects based on customer requirements, including BOM and
			change-management process analysis.
		</p>

		<h2>Education</h2>
		<p class="cv-sub">
			<strong>M.S. in Systems Engineering</strong> · Ajou University · 2024–2026
		</p>
		<p class="cv-sub">
			<strong>B.S. in Naval Architecture &amp; Ocean Engineering</strong> · Inha University · 2012–2019
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.profile {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 2.5em;
	}
	.profile img {
		width: 180px;
		height: 180px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		object-fit: cover;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
	}
	.profile .name {
		margin-top: 0.8em;
		margin-bottom: 0;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.cv {
		margin-top: 3em;
		border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
		padding-top: 1.5em;
	}
	.cv h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 0.6em;
	}
	.cv h2:first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	.cv-head {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 1rem;
	}
	.cv-head .org {
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.cv-head .period {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}
	.cv-sub {
		margin: 0.6em 0 1.2em 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		font-size: 0.98rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	.cv-sub strong {
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.cv-head {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 0.2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
